	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=142431"><span id=" ">BlargX</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">40 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.96]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Well, the monster is much harder than any monster you had to kill to reach him, by a long way. But you can kill him with lesser numbers than you'd want to bother running up through the courtyard and pyramid with.&nbsp;&nbsp;A friend and I have killed him, both of us two-boxing, a few times.  I've killed him in other groups many times and gotten a number of the masks.  One of the better, if not the best, melee droppable masks out at this point.  Never an amygdalan staff.<br/><br/>Getting him without getting a single friend as an add-on proved troublesome to us.  I doubt a cleric duo would find it easy at all.  I seem to remember crippling him fine myself(shaman) every time.<br/><br/>The camp is indeed super boring, though enjoyable easy once you get it down to singles via timing attacks on first one side of the top of the pyramid, then the other.  The experience is lousy though.  That makes it very boring.  Especially when you know that nearby lizards drop tae ew bloods and, at the bottom of the pyramid, fleshgrinders and cure poison rings(we've gotten both, the fleshgrinders not terribly rare either).  It's not really a place you'd want to camp; we've tried it several times and given up.  Just check with tracking every once in a while, and be on your way if the mob isn't up.<br/><br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Blarg, 65 Shaman</td></tr>
